5:
After talking with all our friends, I
learned that all our futures held
something different.
7:
Some of us started new journeys...
while others continued old ones.
14:
Winter has passed, and the cherry
blossoms are blooming at 100%
capacity.
18:
Spring is a both a time of goodbyes
and new beginnings. Nephtim
expresses gratitude to everyone
who made it possible for us to be
here.
21:
As students, we are grateful for this
chance to study, engage in
extracurricular activities, meet new
people... and...
24:
Nephtim wants us all to enjoy this
experience to the fullest.
26:
We will work hard, and we will play
hard. Loneliness levels will be kept to
a minimum.
29:
Making friendship our primary
directive, our time together is
guaranteed to be hella lit.
36:
May all of our darkest nights be
behind us. And all of our brightest
days be ahead.
39:
We will shatter the night and bring
forth a new dawn... together!
44:
The time has come to say goodbye...
*sniffle* Nnngh... I don't wanna go...
48:
You're the one who made this call in
the first place, Little Miss Saint.
You've got people to see and holy
duties to attend to, dontcha?
53:
Oh hush, you old coot! I heard you
whining about it during the wrap
party, too!
57:
Palpebra, Shibuya, and every other
world in between... It will be quite
some time before our paths cross
once more. So it looks like this is
goodbye for now.
65:
Heh heh! It's time for our next
adventure... and no one does
adventure like a pirate! I'm gonna
make Czarina proud!
69:
Up and at 'em, Mermaid Pirates! It's
time to set sail for the northern
waters!
77:
Hah hah hah! You there! Are you
feeling all right? Truly?! Fear not! For
though I may falter, my trusty Lord's
Aegis shan't let you down! Probably.
82:
C-could you at least pretend to
have a little more confidence?!
87:
He's living life his own way—nothing
could be more BEAUTIFUL!
95:
Ahhh... Qualia City never changes,
eh Teurgis?
103:
Whuh... wait. I... I hit my target! Did
you see that?! I did it!
113:
Here, Nao. I packed you some food.
It's only about a day's worth, but I
hope you like it. You're not forgetting
anything, are you?
118: Nope. I'm all set to go!
127: Oh, wow! You finished the book?
135:
This is the first volume.
...I'll be starting volume two next.
137:
I plan to write about everyone's
futures, too.
140:
Our worlds are all connected now.
Nothing has to keep us apart
anymore.
144:
And that's why, this time, I'll be the
one to visit your worlds!
149:
Guess we gotta have lots of stories
prepared for each other, eh? For
next time.
154:
...Yumu, you're coming with us on
our next expedition, right?
158:
Yeah. I'll still keep up my chef
training, though. I've already moved
in and started work at the
restaurant.
161:
But you'd better not be late for our
missions, Nao. Otherwise, I'll have to
come and get you myself.
166:
I know, geez... How'd I ever end up
with such a worrywart for a brother?
170:
Speaking of being late, I've gotta go.
Bye, Yumu!
178: Well... I'd better get going myself.
193:
"And that fateful spring passed like
the warm breeze." A fitting end to a
grand epic.
197:
Stella, you should be proud! You
have made a fine book indeed!
200:
Now let us get this volume to the
printing press, posthaste! Shall I
make a reservation?
205:
Not yet! We still have extra copies to
hand out!
208:
I still don't know what to write for the
second volume...
212:
Mmm. When your first creation is a
masterpiece, making a sequel can
prove difficult.
215:
But the most important thing is that
you are having fun. Did you enjoy
making your first book, Stella?
220:
Yes, very much... I had a wonderful
time!
224: Then that is all that matters!
229:
It's the gravity powers, man. I just
know it.
235:
That's gotta be it, right? Some kinda
give-and-take thing. I mean, why
else would I be the only one who
hasn't gotten any taller?!
240:
*sigh* Are you going to order
anything, Sho? I've got a restaurant
to run here.
245:
I'll have my regular, please. And
could I get my coffee after my meal
this time?
249:
Yeah, yeah... You're in here so much I
should just give you a job, Nova.
259: Whoa! Hey, Yuki! Long time no—huh?!
265:
Sorry to barge in like this, honey! I
practically begged Yuki to bring us
along.
270:
Sure is a nice place you're working
at, son. I like it already.
275:
Aw, man... Dad always was a curry
lover. Now I'll never be able to get
him out of my hair...
280:
And it's not just the two of them,
either. There's another very special
customer right behind us!
285:
*grumble* What's the big deal? I
need to eat, too.
289:
Alk, I'd like some of your red soup...
and your new specialty.
298: Sure thing! And for you, Leve?
303:
I don't care what it is... as long as it
tastes good. Just give me the most
delicious thing you've got.
308:
Coming right up! I'll make this the
best curry you've ever had!
